## Summary

# Session Summary

## Skill Context
- Used `git-memento-workflow` because the work focused on `git memento` note-generation, provider integration, and note-sync behavior.

## Objective
- Add summary-based note support to `git memento` so commits/amends can store:
  - A reviewed markdown summary in the default notes ref.
  - The full raw session in a separate audit notes ref.

## Main Design Decisions
- Added `--summary-skill <skill|default>` to `commit` and `amend <session-id>`.
- Summary mode behavior:
  - Generate summary via provider CLI command.
  - Show summary to user and require confirmation.
  - If rejected, require a custom prompt and regenerate.
- Dual-note model:
  - `refs/notes/commits`: summarized note.
  - `refs/notes/memento-full-audit`: full session record.
- Added provider summary command config:
  - `memento.<provider>.summary.bin`
  - `memento.<provider>.summary.args`
- Default summary command templates:
  - Codex: `codex exec {prompt}`
  - Claude: `claude -p {prompt}`
- Added default summary-skill mapping to in-repo `session-summary-default`.

## Implementation Scope
- Updated CLI parsing/domain/program flow for new flag.
- Extended provider/config/init flows for summary command execution.
- Updated commit/amend workflows for summary approval + dual-note writes.
- Updated git notes service to support non-default notes refs.
- Updated notes sync behavior to include full-audit notes ref.
- Added/updated docs and skill files in both repo and local skill install.

## Verification Outcome
- Full test suite passed after resolving F# syntax/type issues.
- Documentation updated to include:
  - New flag usage.
  - Confirmation/regeneration flow.
  - Dual-ref verification commands.
  - Provider summary config keys.

## Open Review Findings (Not Yet Resolved)
- **P1**: Summary prompt does not include transcript content, which can produce ungrounded summaries if provider command does not independently fetch session data.
- **P2**: Dual-note writes are not atomic; failure writing full-audit note can leave partial state (summary written, audit missing).
